-- Toshiba, Intel, Samsung Electronics to Ally on Chip Design, Nikkei Says
-- B y   H e a t h e r   B u r k e
-- 2010-10-28T17:06:35Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-28/toshiba-intel-samsung-to-develop-chip-technology-nikkei-says.html
Toshiba Corp., Intel Corp. and
Samsung Electronics Co. are working to develop technologies to
reduce chip line widths by more than half to about 10 nanometers
by 2016, Nikkei English News reported, without saying where it
got the information.  The companies may invite about 10 semiconductor-related
companies to join, including JSR Corp. and Dai Nippon Printing
Co., Nikkei said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Heather Burke at 
 hburke2@bloomberg.net  